trans-unit.source: Serves as the primary control in the Web Parts control set for hosting <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart"></xref> controls on a Web page.
trans-unit.target: Fungerer som den primære kontrollen i webdeler kontrollen som er angitt for vert <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart"> </xref> vises på en webside.

trans-unit.source: Within the Web Parts control set, a zone is a region on a Web page that contains Web Parts controls.
trans-unit.target: En sone er et område på en side som inneholder webdeler kontroller i settet webdeler kontrollen.

trans-unit.source: A Web Parts zone is created by a zone control, which is a type of <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.CompositeControl> designed to contain other controls.
trans-unit.target: En webdeler sone er opprettet av en zone-kontrollen som er en type for <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.CompositeControl>som inneholder andre kontroller.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.CompositeControl>

trans-unit.source: The primary functions of a zone are to lay out the controls it contains, and to provide a common user interface (UI) for those controls.
trans-unit.target: De primære funksjonene i en sone er å sette opp Kontroller den inneholder, og oppgi en vanlig brukergrensesnittet (UI) for kontrollene.

trans-unit.source: For general information about zones and how they are used in Web Parts applications, see the base <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebZone> class, and [Web Parts Control Set Overview](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md).
trans-unit.target: Hvis du vil ha generell informasjon om soner og hvordan de brukes i webdeler programmer, kan du se base <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebZone>klassen, og [deler kontrollen angitt oversikt over Web](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md).</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebZone>

trans-unit.source: A key feature of Web Parts controls is that they allow end users to modify (or personalize) Web pages according to their preferences, and save their personalized settings for future browser sessions.
trans-unit.target: En nøkkel funksjon i webdeler kontroller er de Tillat sluttbrukerne mulighet til å endre (eller tilpasse) nettsider i henhold til innstillingene, og lagre sine personlige innstillinger for fremtidige nettleseren økter.

trans-unit.source: One aspect of modifying Web Parts pages includes the ability to add <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> controls or other server controls to a Web Parts page.
trans-unit.target: En side ved å endre webdeler sidene inkluderer muligheten til å legge til <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>Kontroller eller andre serverkontroller til siden for webdeler.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>

trans-unit.source: The CatalogZone control provides a list or catalog of controls that users can add to a page.
trans-unit.target: Kontrollen CatalogZone inneholder en liste eller en katalog med kontrollene som brukere kan legge til en side.

trans-unit.source: The CatalogZone control is one of the fundamental controls in the Web Parts control set.
trans-unit.target: Kontrollen CatalogZone er én av de grunnleggende kontrollene i webdeler kontrollen settet.

trans-unit.source: It derives from the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZoneBase> class, and most of its behavior is inherited from that class.
trans-unit.target: Det er avledet fra <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZoneBase>klassen, og de fleste av den er arvet fra denne klassen.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZoneBase>

trans-unit.source: The CatalogZone class essentially adds to the base class a zone template, which is an implementation of the <xref:System.Web.UI.ITemplate> interface.
trans-unit.target: Klassen CatalogZone i hovedsak legger til basisklassen zone-mal, som er en implementering av den <xref:System.Web.UI.ITemplate>grensesnittet.</xref:System.Web.UI.ITemplate>

trans-unit.source: The zone template enables developers to declaratively add <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart> controls to a zone in the page persistence format.
trans-unit.target: Malen sone gjør det mulig for utviklere å legge til deklarativt <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart>Kontroller til en sone formatet siden utholdenhet.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart>

trans-unit.source: > [!IMPORTANT] > A CatalogZone zone can contain only <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart> controls, and conversely, <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart> controls can reside only in zones that derive from the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZoneBase> class, such as CatalogZone.
trans-unit.target: > [!IMPORTANT] > A CatalogZone sone kan bare inneholde <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart>kontroller, og derimot <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart>Kontroller kan ligge i soner avledes fra de <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZoneBase>klasse, for eksempel CatalogZone.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZoneBase> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart>

trans-unit.source: A CatalogZone control becomes visible only when a user switches a Web page to catalog display mode (<xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager.CatalogDisplayMode>).
trans-unit.target: En kontrollen CatalogZone vises bare når en bruker bytter en webside katalogen visningsmodus (<xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager.CatalogDisplayMode>).</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager.CatalogDisplayMode>

trans-unit.source: A catalog can contain several types of <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart> controls.
trans-unit.target: En katalog kan inneholde flere typer <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart>Kontroller.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart>

trans-unit.source: Each <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart> control is a type of container that contains the server controls users can add to the page.
trans-unit.target: Hver <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart>kontrollen er en beholder som inneholder serverkontroller brukerne kan legge til siden.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart>

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart> controls differ according to where the server controls they contain are coming from.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart>kontrollene er forskjellige i henhold til der serverkontroller de inneholder kommer fra.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart>

trans-unit.source: The following table summarizes the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart> controls provided with the Web Parts control set and, for each control, what kind of server controls it contains.
trans-unit.target: Tabellen nedenfor viser den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart>kontrollerer angitt med webdeler kontrollen angitt og for hver kontroll, hva slags server kontrollerer den inneholder.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart>

trans-unit.source: |Control|Description| |-------------|-----------------| |<xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PageCatalogPart>|Maintains references to controls that have been closed on a page.
trans-unit.target: | Kontrollen | Beskrivelse | |-------------|-----------------| | <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PageCatalogPart>| Opprettholder referanser til kontroller som har blitt lukket på en side.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PageCatalogPart>

trans-unit.source: These controls can be reopened (added back to the page) by users.| |<xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.DeclarativeCatalogPart>|Contains references to controls that are declared in a Web Parts catalog in the markup of a Web page.
trans-unit.target: Disse kontrollene kan åpnes på nytt (tillagt tilbake til siden) av brukere. | | <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.DeclarativeCatalogPart>| Inneholder referanser til kontroller som er angitt i en katalog for webdeler i koden for en webside.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.DeclarativeCatalogPart>

trans-unit.target: Disse kontroller kan legges til en webside av brukere. | | <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.ImportCatalogPart>| Gir Brukergrensesnittet for brukere å laste opp en fil (en XML-fil med en. Webdelen filtype og et angitt format som inneholder tilstandsinformasjon) for en kontroll som en katalog, slik at kontrollen kan legges til en webside. | Fordi klassen CatalogZone legger til bare en mal for sonen virkemåten til basisklassen, den har noen medlemmer.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.ImportCatalogPart>

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZone.%23ctor%2A> constructor is a default constructor; with it, you can initialize a new instance of the CatalogZone class.
trans-unit.target: I <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZone.%23ctor%2A>konstruktøren, er en standardkonstruktør; den. Du kan bruke til å initialisere en ny forekomst av klassen CatalogZone.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZone.%23ctor%2A>

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZone.ZoneTemplate%2A> property gets or sets a reference to the <xref:System.Web.UI.ITemplate> object that contains the controls for the zone.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZone.ZoneTemplate%2A>egenskapen henter eller angir en referanse til det <xref:System.Web.UI.ITemplate>objektet som inneholder kontroller for sonen.</xref:System.Web.UI.ITemplate> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZone.ZoneTemplate%2A>

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZone.CreateCatalogParts%2A> method is critical.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZone.CreateCatalogParts%2A>metoden er kritiske.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZone.CreateCatalogParts%2A>

trans-unit.source: It overrides the base method to create the collection of all <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart> controls contained within the zone template.
trans-unit.target: Den overstyrer base hvordan du oppretter samlingen av alle <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart>Kontroller i zone-malen.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart>

trans-unit.source: > [!NOTE] > The buttons in the CatalogZone UI require client-side scripting in order to work correctly.
trans-unit.target: > [!NOTE] > Knappene CatalogZone UI krever klientside for å fungere på riktig måte.

trans-unit.source: If scripting is disabled in the browser, the user will not be able to perform actions through the CatalogZone UI.
trans-unit.target: Hvis skripting er deaktivert i nettleseren, er ikke brukeren kan utføre handlinger ved hjelp av CatalogZone UI.

trans-unit.source: Accessibility The markup rendered by default for this control might not conform to accessibility standards such as the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines 1.0 (WCAG) priority 1 guidelines.
trans-unit.target: Tilgjengelighet markup gjengis som standard for denne kontrollen, kan ikke med kravene for tilgjengelighet standarder som Web innhold tilgjengelighet retningslinjene 1.0 (WCAG) prioritet 1 retningslinjene.

trans-unit.source: For details about accessibility support for this control, see [ASP.NET Controls and Accessibility](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md).
trans-unit.target: For mer informasjon om tilgjengelighet støtte for denne kontrollen, kan du se [ASP.NET-kontroller og tilgjengelighet](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md).

trans-unit.source: Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZone"></xref> class.
trans-unit.target: Initialiserer en ny forekomst av den <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZone"> </xref> klasse.

trans-unit.source: Because the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZone> control implements a zone template, it is usually used declaratively and you will seldom need to create a new instance of the class using the CatalogZone constructor.
trans-unit.target: Fordi den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZone>kontrollen implementerer en mal for sonen, den brukes vanligvis deklarativt og sjelden må du opprette en ny forekomst av klassen med CatalogZone-konstruktøren.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZone>

trans-unit.source: However, if you inherit from the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZone> class to create a custom zone, you might wish to use the constructor to initialize some of its property values and customize its appearance.
trans-unit.target: Men hvis du arve fra den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZone>klassen for å opprette en egendefinert sone du vil bruke konstruktøren til å initialisere noen av egenskapsverdiene og tilpasse utseendet.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZone>

trans-unit.source: Creates an instance of each <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart"></xref> type that is declared in the zone.
trans-unit.target: Oppretter en forekomst av hver <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart"> </xref> type som er deklarert i sonen.

trans-unit.source: The CreateCatalogParts method is a critical method because when a user switches a page to catalog display mode, this method creates all the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart> controls that make up the Web Parts catalog.
trans-unit.target: Metoden CreateCatalogParts er en kritisk fordi når en bruker bytter en side til katalogen visningsmodus, denne metoden, oppretter alle de <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart>kontrollene som utgjør webdeler-katalogen.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart>

trans-unit.source: The CreateCatalogParts method in the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZone> class provided with the Web Parts control set can create any server control that inherits from the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart> class.
trans-unit.target: Metoden CreateCatalogParts i <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZone>klassen som er angitt med webdeler kontrollen settet kan opprette en serverkontroll som arver fra <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart>klasse.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZone>

trans-unit.source: So, if you create a custom <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart> control and declare it on a page within a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZone> control, this method will create your control when a user switches the page to catalog mode.
trans-unit.target: Hvis du oppretter en egendefinert <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart>kontrollere og deklarere på en side i en <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZone>kontroll, denne metoden oppretter kontrollen når en bruker bytter siden i katalogmodus.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZone> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart>

trans-unit.source: However, for various reasons you might want control over the CreateCatalogParts method.
trans-unit.target: For ulike årsaker du imidlertid ha kontroll over CreateCatalogParts-metoden.

trans-unit.source: You might want it to create only certain <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart> controls.
trans-unit.target: Du kan vil lage bare enkelte <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart>Kontroller.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart>

trans-unit.source: For example, suppose you create a set of custom <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart> controls that have a consistent appearance and belong to a single product or organization.
trans-unit.target: Sett du oppretter et egendefinert <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart>Kontroller som har gjennomført og hører til en enkelt produkt eller organisasjon.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart>

trans-unit.source: If you want page developers to be limited to using those custom controls in a catalog, then you should inherit from the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZone> class, override the CreateCatalogParts method, and allow the method to create only controls of the same type as your custom controls.
trans-unit.target: Hvis du vil at siden utviklerne er begrenset til ved hjelp av disse egendefinerte kontroller i en katalog, bør du skal arve fra den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZone>klasse overstyre metoden CreateCatalogParts og Tillat metoden til å opprette bare kontroller av samme type som de egendefinerte kontrollene.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZone>

trans-unit.source: A <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPartCollection"></xref> with references to all the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart"></xref> controls in the zone.
trans-unit.target: En <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPartCollection"> </xref> med referanser til alle de <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart"> </xref> kontroller i sonen.

trans-unit.source: The current <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart"></xref> control does not have an ID.
trans-unit.target: Gjeldende <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart"> </xref> kontrollen ikke har en ID.

trans-unit.source: Gets or sets a template to contain child controls within a <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZone"></xref> control in page persistence format.
trans-unit.target: Henter eller angir en mal skal inneholde underordnede kontroller for en <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZone"> </xref> kontroll på sider utholdenhet.

trans-unit.source: The ZoneTemplate property references a template of type <xref:System.Web.UI.ITemplate> that is used to contain the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart> controls in the zone.
trans-unit.target: Egenskapen ZoneTemplate refererer til en mal av typen <xref:System.Web.UI.ITemplate>som brukes til å inneholde den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart>Kontroller i sonen.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart> </xref:System.Web.UI.ITemplate>

trans-unit.source: The zone template enables page developers to declare the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart> controls they want to use in persistence format, rather than having to create all the controls programmatically.
trans-unit.target: Malen sone kan siden utviklere deklarere den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart>Kontroller de vil bruke utholdenhet format i stedet for at du må opprette alle kontrollene programmatisk.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart>

trans-unit.source: The set accessor for the ZoneTemplate property calls the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZoneBase.InvalidateCatalogParts%2A> method, which forces the collection of <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart> controls that are declared in the zone template on the page to be refreshed.
trans-unit.target: Angi aksessor for ZoneTemplate egenskapen kall av <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZoneBase.InvalidateCatalogParts%2A>metode, som tvinger samlingen av <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart>Kontroller som er angitt i malen sone på siden oppdateres.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZoneBase.InvalidateCatalogParts%2A>

trans-unit.source: This ensures that the collection of controls referenced by the zone remains current whenever a user changes the controls actually declared within the template on the page.
trans-unit.target: Dette sikrer at samlingen av kontroller refererer til sonen forblir gjeldende når en bruker endrer kontrollene faktisk deklarert i malen på siden.

trans-unit.source: An <xref href="System.Web.UI.ITemplate"></xref> that acts as a container for child controls in the zone.
trans-unit.target: En <xref href="System.Web.UI.ITemplate"> </xref> som fungerer som en beholder for underordnede kontroller i sonen.
